Former Minister of Transport, Hon. Chibuike Amaechi yesterday promised to complete the railways project from Portharcourt to Maiduguri and extend it to Gombe, if elected President. Amaechi who stated this while canvassing for Gombe delegates vote in the forthcoming All Progressive Congress APC primary said he has come to the realization that Gombe by its location is the hub of North East. He warned delegates not to vote for anyone who will not continue the railway project started by President Muhammadu Buhari adding that it takes a lot of courage and determination on the part of the president to be able to so.   Over 10,000 electoral officers to handle Ekiti guber…     Saraki: I have capacity to unite Nigeria     Bayelsa council boss woos delegates with employment letters   “I know what it takes President Buhari to do this project and if not for his determination and courage to continue with it irrespective of so many pressure, we would not have been able to. I know the contract have been awarded and we are already sourcing for funds for it. So I will urge you not to vote for whosoever does not know about this railways project because he will not be able to continue with it,” he said. On the issue of insecurity plaguing the North East in particular, Amaechi said wherever there is huge number of unemployed youths an upsurge in crime becomes inevitable. According to him, Gombe State has a vast land space to engage in large scale agriculture that can help in industrializing the state.